      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REIGN MAKER (2) has been tackling stronger opposition than this of late and while down the track in his last two outings at Penrith he did a good job to come from wider for a 1.5m second at Menangle three back. In a new yard and looks well served by this barrier. IM NO GIFT (3) has not raced for four-and-a-half months but looks forward enough for the return after a minor placing in a recent trial. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw. COUNTRY MAJOR (10) deserves a win following a string of top-three finishes. Draws on the back row but came from there to place the last two times he raced at this venue. GALVARINO (4) was a beaten favourite last time but is a player if he shows the form that saw him kick off the campaign with a second at this venue last month.",
